docs.abstract: Salesforce’s deal to buy the business tools maker Tableau, its largest ever acquisition, was pushed by the need to make business information understandable.
docs.snippet: Salesforce’s deal to buy the business tools maker Tableau, its largest ever acquisition, was pushed by the need to make business information understandable.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Technology vendors have been going on for years about the rising value of data. But information that can’t be understood is not worth much.

headline.main: Making Data Coherent Drives Salesforce’s $15.3 Billion Deal for Tableau
headline.print_headline: Salesforce Makes $15.3 Billion Deal to Buy Tableau

docs.abstract: Learn three strategies that sales leaders use to make their teams more efficient, responsive, and adaptive.
docs.snippet: Learn three strategies that sales leaders use to make their teams more efficient, responsive, and adaptive.
docs.lead_paragraph: If you ask CEOs what their most pressing priority is, the majority will answer in one word: growth. They promise their investors that they will increase revenue at twice the market average (according to Bain research). But at the same time, less than two-thirds of their salespeople are hitting their quotas. So how do CEOs meet their investors’ expectations?

headline.main: Take the Guesswork Out of Growth
